data.title: Al Jefferson, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Al Jefferson stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Al Jefferson - Points

Al Jefferson scores a career high 40 points (2008)

On January 27, 2008, Al Jefferson tied his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 40 points in Minnesota's home win against New Jersey, 98-95. He also had 19 rebounds, 3 assists, 1 steal and 2 blocks. He shot 13/21 from two, shooting at 61.9% from the field. He also shot 14/17 from the free-throw line.

Al Jefferson - Rebounds

Al Jefferson grabs a career high 26 rebounds (2010)

On January 13, 2010, Al Jefferson tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 26 rebounds in Minnesota's road loss against Houston, 120-114. He also had 26 points, 1 assist, 1 steal and 1 block.

Al Jefferson - Assists

Al Jefferson gives a career high 7 assists (2012)

On March 05, 2012, Al Jefferson tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 7 assists in Utah's road win against Cleveland, 100-109. He also had 25 points, 13 rebounds, 1 steal and 3 blocks.

Al Jefferson - Steals

Al Jefferson has a career high 4 steals (2007)

On December 08, 2007, Al Jefferson tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 4 steals in Minnesota's home win against Phoenix, 100-93. He also had 32 points, 20 rebounds and 2 assists.

Al Jefferson - Blocks

Al Jefferson blocks a career high 7 shots (2010)

On December 22, 2010, Al Jefferson tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 7 blocks in Utah's road win against Minnesota, 107-112. He also had 23 points, 9 rebounds and 1 assist.

Al Jefferson - Efficiency

Al Jefferson records a career high 53 efficiency rating (2008)

On January 27, 2008, Al Jefferson set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 53 efficiency in Minnesota's home win against New Jersey, 98-95. He also had 40 points, 19 rebounds and 3 assists.
